## How to scan memory

- Scanning for a remembered rule → check `## Feedback` (or `MEMORY-feedback.md` after split)
- Scanning for "where is X" / external-system pointers → check `## Reference` (or `MEMORY-reference.md` after split)
- Scanning for active project state → check `## Project` (always inlined here, even after split)

## How to add new entries

1. Create `<prefix>_<slug>.md` in this directory with frontmatter:

   ```markdown
   ---
   name: <short-kebab-case-slug>
   description: <one-line summary>
   metadata:
     type: <user | feedback | project | reference>
   ---
   ```

2. Append a pointer to the matching section (`feedback_*` → Feedback, `reference_*` → Reference, `project_*` → Project): `- [Title](<filename>.md) — one-line hook under 150 chars`
3. Commit and push to the memory backup repo (if one is configured) so the entry survives off-machine.

